flowRoot.flowPara: CourtListener.com, aims to ease the difficulty of staying up to date with court judgments by providing a free and open source platform for the aggregation, organization, search and retrieval of legal documents. The aggregation of new court documents is completed by a scraper on a rolling basis, building a huge corpus, and providing the latest cases from the FederalCourts of Appeal within on average about fifteen minutes from the moment they are published on the court website. From there, the documentsare quickly indexed, and Atom feeds and document listings are updated. Finally, at the close of each day and beginning of each week and month,alerts are emailed to registered users informing them about topics that they have identified as relevant.
